        <TD VALIGN="TOP" ALIGN="LEFT" WIDTH=693 HEIGHT=133 COLSPAN=3>
                    
                      <div align="left">
                      <table border="0" width="696" height="136">
                        <tr><td width='686' height='19' valign='top' align='left'> <font face='Arial,sans-serif' SIZE=2 COLOR=#ffff80> 2000-07-11 - Scars of Velious Expansion Pack Announced</font> </td></tr><tr><td width='686' height='19'></td></tr><tr><td width='686' height='19' valign='top' align='left'> <font face='Arial,sans-serif' SIZE=2 COLOR=#C0C0C0> <p><span class="newstitle">The &quot;Scars of Velious&quot; Expansion Pack
Announced</span><br>
<span class="newstext">This just in from EQG3 and the <a href="http://www.everlore.com" target="_new">Everlore</a>
site:<br>
</span><span class="newstext">
<blockquote>
  Brad McQuaid just announced that there will be a new expansion based on the
  continent of Velious here at the EverQuest Gathering. He said the expansion
  will be chock full of White dragons Ice giants other cold weather based
  nasties. This December is the expected release date. He has also stated they
  will be upgrading the current character graphics for this expansion. Be sure
  to mark this time down in your calendar because you will for sure want to burn
  some vacation and stock up on no-doze.
</blockquote>
This bit was posted on the <a href="http://www.eqanswers.com" target="_new">EQAnswers</a>
site:
<blockquote>
  <br>
  The new expansion will take place on Velious, the Ice Land, and will not only
  contain new creatures but also an upgrade of the existing graphics engine.
  Among other things, Velious will also have a new starting city for the
  Barbarian race, and feature numerous ports that are rumored to come off from
  the upcoming zone entitled &quot;The Warrens&quot;.
</blockquote>
<br>
</span>
</font> </td></tr><tr><td width='686' height='55' valign='top' align='left'> <font face='Arial,sans-serif' SIZE=2 COLOR=#ffff80> Source: EQ Gathering -  </font> <a href=http://eqgathering.bizland.com/ </a> eqgathering.bizland.com/ </td></tr><tr><td width='686' height='19' valign='top' align='left'> <font face='Arial,sans-serif' SIZE=2 COLOR=#ffff80> 2000-07-11 - More Info on Scars Expansion Pack</font> </td></tr><tr><td width='686' height='19'></td></tr><tr><td width='686' height='19' valign='top' align='left'> <font face='Arial,sans-serif' SIZE=2 COLOR=#C0C0C0> <p><b><font face="Arial" size="3" color="#C0C0C0">The Scars of Velious --
Updated Feature List</font></b><font face="Arial" size="3" color="#C0C0C0"><br>
</font>
<blockquote>
  <font face="verdana" size="2" color="#C0C0C0">The following is a quick run
  down of all known information about The Scars of Velious that was gathered by <a href="http://www.everlore.com">Everlore</a>
  staff members from the EverQuest Gathering III.</font>
  <ul>
    <li><b><font face="verdana" size="2" color="#C0C0C0">One new Continent -
      Velious which contains 12 new zones.</font>
      <li><font face="verdana" size="2" color="#C0C0C0">Brand new character
        graphics.</font>
      <li><font face="verdana" size="2" color="#C0C0C0">Velious will be geared
        towards levels 35-60 players, although the level limit will stay at 60.</font>
      <li><font face="verdana" size="2" color="#C0C0C0">New Starting City for
        Barbarians.</font>
      <li><font face="verdana" size="2" color="#C0C0C0">Velious will focus
        primarily on new zones, quests, items and more variety in how players
        appear in-game.</font>
      <li><font face="verdana" size="2" color="#C0C0C0">Some of the new
        creatures include White Dragons, and frost &amp; storm giants although
        there will be no new player races or classes.</font>
      <li><font face="verdana" size="2" color="#C0C0C0">Official Velious site
        will be up in about a month or so, will include screen shots.</font>
      <li><font face="verdana" size="2" color="#C0C0C0">Currently set for a
        Release Date of December 2000.</font></b></li>
  </ul>
  <p><font face="verdana" size="2" color="#C0C0C0">Some additional notes:<br>
  Viewing the new graphics will be optional.<br>
  Velious will not include the Ruins of Kunark expansion.<br>
  Velious has been in development for awhile now.<br>
  The Original games system requirements will stay the same.<br>
  And lastly Jeff Butler had this to say. &quot;Velious is going to kick
  ass.&quot;</font></p>
</blockquote>

</font> </td></tr><tr><td width='686' height='55' valign='top' align='left'> <font face='Arial,sans-serif' SIZE=2 COLOR=#ffff80> Source: EverLore -  </font> <a href=http://www.everlore.com </a> www.everlore.com </td></tr><tr><td width='686' height='19' valign='top' align='left'> <font face='Arial,sans-serif' SIZE=2 COLOR=#ffff80> 2000-07-11 - Brad Stepping Away for EQ, We think not...</font> </td></tr><tr><td width='686' height='19'></td></tr><tr><td width='686' height='19' valign='top' align='left'> <font face='Arial,sans-serif' SIZE=2 COLOR=#C0C0C0> <font face="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica" size="2"><b><font color="#C0C0C0"><font face="Times New Roman" size="3">Aradune
a Figurehead? </font></font></b></font><font color="#C0C0C0"><b><font face="Times New Roman" size="3">Hmmm...</font></b></font><font face="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica" size="2">
<div>
  <div>
    <font color="#C0C0C0">Brad McQuaid had this to say on the <a href="http://boards.stratics.com/cgi-bin/boards/eq/showflat.pl?Cat=7&amp;Board=eqwestwood&amp;Number=350163&amp;page=0&amp;view=collapsed&amp;sb=5&amp;vc=1" target="_blank">EQSS
    Westwood Tavern</a> in response to rumors that he was no longer directly
    involved with EverQuest:<br>
    </font>
    <blockquote>
      <font face="Times New Roman" size="2" color="#C0C0C0">Theres some truth to
      what youre saying but its not totally accurate.<br>
      <br>
      As VP of Core Games Im responsible for all massively multiplayer games
      Verant/SOE develops. Each project has a Producer in charge of it, and each
      Producer reports to me. Its my job to give time and attention to all the
      projects were working on... fairly equal time, although titles that ship
      sooner always have priority over titles that ship later.<br>
      <br>
      Jeff Butler is Producer of EQ Live and EverQuest Worlds Online: Velious...
      er, EverQuest: The Scars of Velious.<br>
      <br>
      Velious is our next shipping title, btw.<br>
      <br>
      -Brad<br>
      <br>
      Brad McQuaid<br>
      Vice President, Verant Interactive<br>
      Executive Producer, EverQuest</font>
    </blockquote>
  </div>
</div>
</font>

</font> </td></tr><tr><td width='686' height='55' valign='top' align='left'> <font face='Arial,sans-serif' SIZE=2 COLOR=#ffff80> Source: EQ Stratics -  </font> <a href=http://http://eq.stratics.com </a> http://eq.stratics.com </td></tr>    
